The President has signed several laws including the Fort Ontario Study Act, which directs the Secretary of the Interior to study the suitability of designating Fort Ontario as a unit of the National Park System. Another law signed is the Sam Farr and Nick Castle Peace Corps Reform Act of 2018, which amends authorities in the Peace Corps Act concerning Peace Corps volunteers. The Justice Served Act of 2018 authorizes the Department of Justice to award grants to address the backlog of violent crime cases involving suspects identified through DNA evidence. The Veteransâ€™ Compensation Cost-of-Living Adjustment Act of 2018 provides for a cost-of-living adjustment for veterans' disability compensation and dependency compensation. The Small Business Innovation Protection Act of 2017 expands intellectual property education and training for small businesses. The Joseph Sanford Jr. Channel in New York is redesignated as the "Negro Bar Channel", and the Marrakesh Treaty Implementation Act provides for the implementation of the Marrakesh Treaty to facilitate access to published works for persons with disabilities.